challenges.description:
Before writing code, analysis matters. Read the HLSL shader below and list (as GLSL comments) every construct that needs to change when porting to GLSL ES 3.0. Then write the corrected GLSL.

HLSL to analyze:
```hlsl
cbuffer Light : register(b0) {
    float3 lightPos;
    float3 lightColor;
    float3 cameraPos;
};

float4 blinnPhong(float3 pos, float3 normal, float3 albedo) {
    float3 L   = normalize(lightPos - pos);
    float3 V   = normalize(cameraPos - pos);
    float3 H   = normalize(L + V);
    float diff = saturate(dot(normal, L));
    float spec = pow(saturate(dot(normal, H)), 32.0);
    float3 col = albedo * lightColor * diff + lightColor * spec;
    return float4(col, 1.0);
}

float4 main(float3 pos : TEXCOORD0, float3 normal : TEXCOORD1) : SV_Target {
    float3 albedo = lerp(float3(0.2, 0.5, 0.9), float3(0.9, 0.3, 0.1), 0.4);
    return blinnPhong(pos, normalize(normal), albedo);
}
```

In GLSL ES 3.0 (targeting this course's quad renderer):
- cbuffer → `layout(std140) uniform` block (WebGL2 does not support `binding=N` on uniform blocks)
- float3 → vec3, float4 → vec4
- saturate(x) → clamp(x, 0.0, 1.0)
- lerp → mix
- SV_Target → out vec4 fragColor
- No vertex shader varyings available — derive pos and normal procedurally from gl_FragCoord and u_resolution
- No return from main(); write to fragColor

